    // then 'x' can effectively be replaced by 'z' through a chain of operations.
    // The smallest element we can replace a number with is the greatest common divisor (GCD)
    // of the original number and all other elements it can be chained to.

    // Consider the set of all possible values we can replace any element with.
    // If we have elements {n1, n2, ..., nk}, any element n_i can eventually be replaced
    // by some value d, where d divides n_i, and d is present in the set or derived from it.

