    // then 'd' must be a common divisor of all elements involved in the reduction chain.
    // If we can reach a state where all elements are replaced by their greatest common divisor (GCD)
    // with respect to the initial set, that would be the minimum.

    // Let's re-examine the operation: nums[a] -> nums[b] if nums[a] % nums[b] == 0.
    // This means nums[b] is a divisor of nums[a].
    // To minimize the sum, we want every element to become the smallest possible divisor present in the array or reachable.

    // If we find the GCD of all elements in the initial array, let G = gcd(nums[0], nums[1], ..., nums[n-1]).
